post_text: An update on ticket availability for USHS home soccer matches from athletic director Brad Ehrman.
shared_text:
Upper Sandusky E.V. Schools (OH)
August 26 at 8:02 AM ¬∑

USHS Boys/Girls Soccer Ticket Policy (from AD Brad Ehrman):

The North Central Ohio Soccer League (NCOSL) has announced that each member school will be allowed to determine the number of tickets that may be sold and the method for selling them for their home events based on the capacity of their venue. Upper Sandusky High School is a member school for both varsity boys and girls soccer.

USHS will now be selling tickets to all home boys and girls soccer matches at the gate on the day of the game. No vouchers or permits will be needed to purchase tickets due to the large capacity of the home stadium for hosting soccer. Family members, the general public, and students are now welcome to attend. ‚Ä¶

Wyandot Memorial Hospital
June 8 at 9:00 AM ¬∑

Schedule your athletic physical yet? Appointments are still available this week! Select your time by phoning 419-294-4991 extension 2269. post_text: Here, we see a soccer ball in its natural habitat of the yard. This is where this object is the most effective, despite some people who don‚Äôt like to improve in the off season thinking it‚Äôs best kept in a closet or under a bed. Much like it‚Äôs wild counterpart, the domestic soccer ball also likes to be taken out into the yard, even now in times of isolation as it‚Äôs been proven one person can subdue the beast. If you find yourself unable to control a soccer ball on your own, younger siblings have been shown to be effective as alternative ball retrievers. So, take your soccer ball out in fresh air and don‚Äôt leave it in a dark closet. #SoccerBallAbuseAwareness

It is with great pleasure to announce Coach Ty Calvin (left) has verbally accepted the head coach position with the USHS girls soccer team, pending approval of the board of education.

Coach Calvin has been with the program since the 2012 season, serving as an assistant and goalkeeper coach for 2 seasons under Chelsea Porter and 6 seasons under Patrick Massara.

Coach Calvin has announced Asst. Coach James Massara (right) is remaining with the program as well.

Best wishes and thank you for everything you‚Äôve done for the program Coach Patrick Massara (center) and congratulations to Coach Calvin on his acceptance of his new role with the program!

Our Lady Rams have squared up against some tough opponents as 2 of their first 6 opponents are in the top 13 in Division 2 (our ladies will compete in the Division 3 tournament this year).

The program held its end-of-the-year banquet Wednesday evening at Upper Sandusky Moose Lodge #1093.

Award winners were (front row, from left): Alivia Oney, Ohio Scholastic Soccer Coaches Association academic award, All-Northwest OSSCA second team, All-North Central Ohio Soccer Association first team, most valuable player, 4th-year letter winner.; Taylor Norris, All-NWOSSCA honorable mention, All-NCOSA 2nd team, co-offensive player of the year, 3rd-year letter winner; Jenna Rodriguez, All-NWOSSCA honorable mention, All-NCOSA 1st team, defensive player of the year, 4th-year letter winner; Audrey Boes, All-NWOSSCA honorable mention, All-NCOSA honorable mention, co-offensive player of the year, 4th-year letter winner; (back row) Grace Kinley, Knights of Columbus sportsmanship award; Lindsay Weininger, co-rookie of the year; Grace Vent, co-rookie of the year; Cortni Brown, All-NCOSA honorable mention, most improved, 3rd-year letter winner; and Brooke Swavel, All-NCOSA honorable mention, co-rookie of the year.

post_text:
What a great honor for Charlotte Leeth & Lana Sakash! We partnered with them this spring to send a soccer donation to Rativtsi, Ukraine!

"This year, the humanitarian goal was to bring soccer equipment to the children. With the help of the Upper Sandusky, Bluffton and Cory-Rawson boys and girls soccer teams, as well as local donations, they were able to bring several bins worth of equipment to share with the children."

‚ÄúThe jerseys were great, but kids still need soccer shoes and soccer shorts,‚Äù Sakash said. ‚ÄúIt will be winter by the time this next donation arrives there, so they could also use warm clothes and boots if possible.‚Äù

"Donations are being accepted by Whole Life Fitness at 228 S. Eighth St., Upper Sandusky, with a tentative cut-off date of Nov. 1."

Please read the Daily Chief Union article from Saturday 9/30 for the full story and donation information!
<http://www.dailychiefunion.com/featured/leeth-sakash-honored-in-ukraine/>

post_text: 2015 USHS graduate and Huntington University player Jaime Calvin is offering individual/group training this summer! If interested, please contact her directly. See her information below:
shared_text:
Jaime Calvin‚ÄéUSHS Girls Soccer
April 18, 2017 at 8:19 PM ¬∑

Soccer Summer Training
What: The idea of this camp is to get the player in better shape while focusing most of our time on soccer. This is for grades 1-8.

When: Starting May 16th and running every Tuesday and Thursday until July 13th. A total of 18 sessions. The time for these sessions is still TBD.

Where: Training sessions will be held at the high school fields.

Why: This is a great opportunity for players who do not want to play club to be learning the same things without the travel and the cost.

Cost: The cost for these sessions will be a total of $10 due at the first session.

If you are interested in individual training please contact me and we can set that up as well. Individual training will be $20 for 18 sessions.

Please contact me to register for this camp at 419-310-9193 (texting is preferred) or email me at calvinj@huntington.edu

I am also open to helping current high school girls as either a group of 4 or as individuals. Also $10 each for a group or $20 for individuals.

Upper Sandusky Youth Soccer
October 9, 2016 at 6:03 PM ¬∑

USYS coaches took 5 teams to the 2016 Findlay Fall Classic tournament this weekend and out of the 35 teams that attended, we had 3 teams in the championships.

The U12 Upper Sandusky Divas placed 1st in the U12 girls division! They also shut out every team! Way to go Divas!

The U12 Upper Sandusky Crew placed 1st in the U12 Co-ed/boys division! Way to go Crew!

And in the U15 division Upper Sandusky Black took 2nd place! Way to go Black!

Congratulations to all the Coaches for all the hard work and dedication!

Thanks to all the parents for the Support, we couldn't do it with out you!

#RamPride

*** I'm asking all girls soccer alumni for some help! ***
I've been working on making a complete history of the girls soccer program so we can put up a record board. However, I've only managed to find books from 2011-current. If anyone has a scrapbook of newspaper clippings that list goals, assists, saves, etc. for seasons 2003-2010 PLEASE let me borrow them! I'd like to put together a complete program history! =)

post_text: Shoutout to the Upper Sandusky Youth Soccer U10 Lil Divas for their undefeated spring season & being a part of the Columbus Crew SC "Night of Champions" this past Saturday! #LadyRamPride
shared_text:
Upper Sandusky Youth Soccer
June 28, 2016 at 1:36 PM ¬∑

The U10 Lil Divas had a Saturday to remember this past weekend as they were recognized during the "Night of Champions" at MAPFRE Stadium for the Columbus Crew SC vs New York Red Bulls match! The coaches and ladies were able to be on the field during player introductions and national anthem.

The Lil Divas were 9-0 this spring season and won the Riverdale Tournament! Thank you to all those who made this memory happen!
